  "title": "Question on the page \"connectMenu\"",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js. I could not find what I was looking for on the page \"[connectMenu](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/connectors/connectMenu.html)\".\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe what you're looking for here. -->\r\n\r\nHello! I am using Algolia search in my WordPress website, however apparently wp plugin doesnot support menuSelect widget, yet. So I tried to create connectMenu using example [here](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/connectors/connectMenu.html#example). It worked perfectly, however I would like to add a select option that will clear current selected refine value, just what menuSelect does (something similar to 'see all' default option).  \r\nP.S. I also tried to create custom template and enqueue latest instantsearch.js files from cdn, yet menuSelect widget didnot work, not sure what could go wrong there. I disabled algolia front-end search in plugin settings. \r\nThank you.",
